<body>
    <h1>Minecraft Controller & Download Guide</h1>

    <h2>Using a Minecraft Controller</h2>
    <p>
        Minecraft can be played with various controllers. Follow these steps to set up your controller:
    </p>
    <ol>
        <li>Connect your controller to your computer.</li>
        <li>Open Minecraft and go to the Settings menu.</li>
        <li>Find the "Controls" section and customize your controller settings.</li>
        <li>Save your changes and start playing Minecraft with your controller!</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Downloading Minecraft</h2>
    <p>
        Here's a step-by-step guide on how to download Minecraft:
    </p>
    <ol>
        <li>Visit the official Minecraft website: <a href="https://www.minecraft.net/" target="_blank">https://www.minecraft.net/</a></li>
        <li>Click on the "Get Minecraft" button.</li>
        <li>Choose the edition of Minecraft you want to download (Java Edition or Bedrock Edition).</li>
        <li>Follow the on-screen instructions to complete the purchase (if required).</li>
        <li>Once purchased, log in to your Minecraft account.</li>
        <li>Go to the "Downloads" section and download the installer for your operating system.</li>
        <li>Run the installer and follow the installation instructions.</li>
        <li>Launch Minecraft and start playing!</li>
    </ol>

    <p>
        Enjoy your Minecraft experience with your controller!
    </p>
